Ukraineâ€™s farmers harvested
15.9 million metric tons of grain this season to July 20,
agricultural researcher UkrAgroConsult said.  Average grain yields declined to 2.22 tons a hectare (2.47
acres) from 2.89 tons a hectare a year earlier, the Kiev-based
researcher said in e-mailed statement today.  Wheat, including winter and spring crop, accounted for
10.6 million tons with an average yield of 2.46 tons a hectare,
according to the researcher. The barley harvest was 4.7 million
tons with an average yield 1.85 tons a hectare.  Grain was harvested from 7.2 million hectares this season
compared with 6.69 million hectares a year earlier, the
researcher said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
